Paper: hep-th/9512025

Date: 1995-12-05

Title: Poisson-Lie T-Duality

Authors: Eugene Tyurin, Rikard von Unge

Comments: 16 pages, plain LaTeX 2e, one paragraph added to the conclusions;

this is the final version accepted by Physics Letters BJournal-ref: Phys.Lett. B382 (1996) 233-240

We formulate Poisson-Lie T-duality in a path-integral manner that allows usto analyze the quantum corrections. Using the path-integral, we rederive themost general form of a Poisson-Lie dualizeable background and the generalizedBuscher transformation rules it has to satisfy.